theorem Topology.compl_closure_subset_interior_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ ⊆ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := by
  classical
  -- The complement of the closure is open.
  have h_open : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) :=
    (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X))).isOpen_compl
  -- The complement of the closure is contained in the complement of `A`.
  have h_subset_compl : ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X)ᶜ := by
    intro x hx
    by_contra hA
    -- `hA : x ∈ A`
    have hx_closure : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hA
    have : False := hx hx_closure
    exact this
  -- Use the maximality property of `interior` to conclude.
  exact interior_maximal h_subset_compl h_open

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_interior_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) = interior A := by
  simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq]
